{
  "stem": "13251.4",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But all the American-- it's, it's like I, I, I came after-- I got-- I tried to, to, to excuse them for their, their attitude, like how many relatives already came from Europe that they showed, you know, enthusiasm or were excited about.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "After a while, it gets to be old, old, you know, old hat, you know.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And by the time I came, it's not a big deal.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And for me it was-- all my life I didn't have a living relative except my brother.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And to discover there's was such a, such a, you know, a-- something to be really get excited about and emotional about.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And when I got this cold shoulder when I came here, it was really a slap in the face.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In fact, I remember I have one relative in Cleveland, very, very wealthy.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And it seems like the more money they have, they think that's what everybody's looking at.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I never asked anybody for anything.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] Even my aunt in New York-- I ended up in Cleveland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I think I'll come to that later.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I didn't leave New York till I paid her back for the, for the transportation that, that she put-- laid out.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, Aunt Gizella.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that's the way I am.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "No, I didn't come to America to take advantage of rich relatives, but they seem to have had-- they were very-- they put on this defensive attitude, you know, of all these new immigrants, I think, maybe because of the track record that some of them, you know, you know, did, did ask for-- you know, you're American.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Help me, you know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In fact, I have-- back to this very wealthy cousin that I have.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
